 And this is what memory looks like. 

00:01:21.081 --> 00:01:26.055
 These things are called modules, but fast guys like me call them "sticks." 

00:01:26.092 --> 00:01:33.154
 You place it in one of the slots on the motherboard - this way. 

00:01:33.190 --> 00:01:40.108
 Now there are usually 2 or 4 or 6 slots on the motherboard. 

00:01:40.163 --> 00:01:46.008
 You don't have to fill them all, but you can, so that's handy. 

